omewhere. I'm also wondering if TypeScript's strict mode or some configuration setting is causing it to reject the property, or if there's something about how the interface is being cached or compiled that's preventing it from being recognized properly. Let me just start fixing the errors directly rather than continuing to trace through the type definitions. I've got several files to update: renaming properties in `GetTeacherRankingsUseCase.ts` from `result` to `docs`, fixing the pagination in `coursesStudents.service.ts`, updating the meta structure in `devices.service.ts` and the exam-related services, and adding a missing `totalPages` field to `leadSources.service.ts`.\n\nNow looking at the remaining fixes needed—there's the lessons service response structure, and then a bunch of controller files that are trying to access `.data` on their response types when those properties don't actually exist on the interfaces. I need to systematically go through each controller and either add the missing `.data` accessor or adjust how it's being used. Let me tackle the most critical ones first and work through them methodically.","thinkingSignature":"25b92fd5b821c6d5479688560ef7de17562f7ea8e73afe38fdfed3b442358eed"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me examine the key files systematically to understand all the mismatches:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r0vtzap7dgmh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"\\.data\\b\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/modules/coursesStudents/coursesStudents.controller.ts | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":138,"output":669,"cacheRead":23703,"cacheWrite":641,"totalTokens":25151,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776135277984,"responseId":"062cdf6f4049606c4deaf23f3adc3a24"}}
